{
  "texts": [
    "Above all, we summarize the literature that ML can be utilized to boost the predetermined target through four angles, including ML potential [78] [79] [80] [81] [82], ML prediction 83, ML analysis 10, 75 and ML inverse learning 84, 85 shown in Fig. 3c.",
    "We will expand with examples based on these four angles correspondingly.",
    "For ML potential, Hajibabaei et al.",
    "79 created universal potentials to simulate Li diffusivity in solid-state conductors, for example, Li-P-S and Li-Sb-S and even quaternary composite ones (e.g., Li-Ge-P-S).",
    "This hierarchical approach paves the way for modeling large-scale complexity."
  ]
}